lyrics:
3 contributorswhiskey lyricsverse 1
whiskey wont you come and take my troubles
cause i cant seem to do it on my own
in the morning there is hours and infinity
the starlit evenings come to take me home

verse 2
i aint got a dime in my pocket
and i just stepped on my last cigarette
but theres a bar downtown thatll give me credit
a home away from home away i went

verse 3
tomorrow theres a train to carolina
tomorrow thats where im gonna go
feel the warm sunshine on my shoulders
and live my days a free and easy soul

verse 4
my home is with the hills and trees around me
my ceiling holds the moon and stars above
so ill never be a lonely man awalking
ill never live one day without love

verse 5
so whiskey wont you come and take my troubles
cause i cant seem to do it on my own
in the morning there is hours and infinity
the starlit evenings come to take me home
